The friar

The church bells softly awoke the monk.
He glided from his rest undisturbed, for his dreamlike soul was at rest.

His room was 5x5x5 feet.
The walls were a patchy cobble.
His bed was sheeps wool sewn into a cloth hide. It slumped within 4 rough wooden paramaters.
His bedside table held a candlestick and a leather-bound bible.

A hazy window near the celing let in a light warmer than most.
On the parralel size, a cross. An iron cross. The intracate detailing 
